messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path: /printshops/{id}/reviews

- allHttpMethodsAllowed: false

- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The controller class has no class-level @RequestMapping, so the method-level paths are full paths as written.
- The getPrintShopReviews method is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{id}/reviews", method = RequestMethod.GET) — therefore GET is accepted for /printshops/{id}/reviews.
- The addPrintShopReview method is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{id}/reviews", method = RequestMethod.POST) — therefore POST is accepted for /printshops/{id}/reviews.
- There are PUT and DELETE handlers in this file, but they are mapped to /printshops/{printShopId}/reviews/{reviewId} (they require the additional {reviewId} path segment), so they do not apply to /printshops/{id}/reviews.
- No mappings for HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, or PATCH appear in the code for this exact path; per your instruction I did not assume framework-provided implicit handling — only methods explicitly declared in the source were counted.
